{
  "texts": [
    "The LOSS attack is a straightforward baseline where the basic idea is if their loss values are less than a specified threshold, then it considers samples as training members [308].",
    "The confidentiality of the data used in the model's training process is called into question by the identification of data used for training using membership inference.",
    "These type of attacks poses serious privacy concerns, particularly in scenarios where the targeted model has undergone training on sensitive information, e.g., medical or financial data [256].",
    "Shokri et al.",
    "first introduced MIA against ML Model (MIA-ML) [239]."
  ]
}